---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Accessibility Statement" description="Accessibility statement for Spark Lane Dev">
  <div class="container accessibility-wrapper">   
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">Accessibility Statement</h1>
    
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p class="lead text-lg mb-8">
        This website (sparklane.dev) is frequently updated and is consistently built with care and intention. The web should be a friendly and accessible place for everyone. I aim to develop inclusively, aiming to provide good usability across a range of abilities, devices, and situations.
      </p>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 mt-8">My accessibility standards</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        I aim to meet <strong>WCAG 2.2 to Level AA standard</strong> as a minimum throughout the site.
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-gray-800/5 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8 dark:bg-gray-200/5">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">Core practices</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Level AA</h4>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm">
              <li>semantic HTML5 with clear heading structure</li>
              <li>skip link to main content</li>
              <li>responsive, zoom-friendly layout (up to 200%)</li>
              <li>keyboard-accessible navigation and links</li>
              <li>custom focus styles for visibility</li>
              <li>alt text for meaningful images, decorative images hidden</li>
              <li>readable font sizes and color contrast of at least 4.5:1</li>
              <li>support for prefers-reduced-motion</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">Level AAA</h4>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm">
              <li>most body text meets or exceeds 7:1 contrast</li>
              <!-- <li>pronunciation hints or language markers for non-English phrases</li> -->
              <li>focus styles are consistent across browsers and high contrast</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 mt-8">Your experience, your way</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">
        You should be able to:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-8">
        <li>use your browser defaults for settings, sizes and styling</li>
        <li>zoom in (or out) without breaking your experience</li>
        <li>navigate the site with just your keyboard</li>
        <li>listen to the site using a screen reader</li>
      </ul>
    <p>
      I also make the website text as simple as possible to understand.
      AbilityNet has advice on <a href="https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/">making your device easier to use</a> if you have a disability.
    </p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 mt-8">How accessible this website is</h2>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="font-medium text-yellow-800 mb-2">
          Parts of this website are not fully accessible. For example:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li>some pages may not be written in plain English</li>
          <li>some images may not have adequate image descriptions</li>
          <li>some heading elements may not be consistent</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    <h2 class="text-xl">Feedback and contact information</h2>
    <p>
      If you need information in a different format, please contact me:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Email: <a href="mailto:emma@sparklane.dev">emma@sparklane.dev</a></li>
      <li>LinkedIn: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/emmalouiselane/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Connect with me on LinkedIn</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      In your message, include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>the web address (URL) of the content</li>
      <li>your email address and name</li>
      <li>the format you need - for example, plain text, large print or audio</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 class="text-xl">Reporting accessibility problems with this website</h2>
    <p>
      If you find any problems that are not listed on this page or you think I'm not meeting accessibility requirements, <a href="mailto:emma@sparklane.dev">contact me</a>.
    </p>
    <h2 class="text-xl">Technical information about this website's accessibility</h2>
    <p>
      I am committed to making this website accessible, in accordance with the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.
    </p>
    <hr />
    <h3>Date</h3>
    <p>
      This statement was created on
      <span class="basic-information statement-created-date">13 December 2025</span>
       using the <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/planning/statements/">W3C Accessibility Statement Generator Tool</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
